summary: Starbucks (SBUX) is making waves with a sweeping $1 billion restructuring plan that includes closing hundreds of stores across North America and cutting about 900 corporate roles. headline: Is Starbucks a Good Value After Record-Breaking Fall Sales?
summary: Trying to make sense of Starbucks’ stock these days? You’re definitely not alone. Whether you’re a longtime believer in the green mermaid or just checking in for a potential buying opportunity, there’s been plenty to watch lately. Over the past year, Starbucks shares have slid by 13.4%, and the stock is even down 11.8% year-to-date. This is pretty notable for a brand with its kind of global presence. Even the last month saw a further decline, slipping 4.8%. Some of this movement ties back to...

headline: Three Starbucks locations in Spokane close after billion dollar restructuring plan announcement
summary: Oct. 7—Starbucks is closing three of its 29 locations in Spokane and its popular Ritzville coffee shop just off Interstate 90. The local closures and many more across Washington come as company CEO Brian Niccol embarks on a $1 billion restructuring plan. The closures began last week and will affect 369 Washington employees, according to a notice filed with Washington's Employment Security ...
